Services (OPES) Callout Protocols
2004", shape=ellipse, URL="RFC3836.html", target="_top", tooltip="This document specifies the requirements that the OPES (Open Pluggable Edge Services) callout protocol must satisfy in order to support the remote execution of OPES services.  The requirements are intended to help evaluate possible protocol candidates, as well as to guide the development of such protocols.  This memo provides information for the Internet community."];
